speech.p:
Motion made, and Question proposed,
That, for the purposes of any Act resulting from the Housing and Urban Development Bill ("the Act"), it is expedient to authorize—


(1) the payment out of money provided by Parliament of—


(a) any sums required to enable the Secretary of State to make payments to the Urban Regeneration Agency ("the Agency");

(b) any expenses of the Secretary of State incurred in consequence of the Act;

(c) any increase attributable to the Act in the sums payable out of money so provided under any other enactment:

(2) the payment out of the National Loans Fund of any sums necessary to enable the Secretary of State to make loans to the Agency;

(3) the payment out of the Consolidated Fund of any sums required to fulfil guarantees given by the Treasury in respect of sums borrowed by the Agency.—[Mr. Arbuthnot.]

Resolved,
That for the purposes of any Act resulting from the Housing and Urban Development Bill ("the Act"), it is expedient to authorize—


(1) the payment out of money provided by Parliament of—

(a) any sums required to enable the Secretary of State to make payments to the Urban Regeneration Agency ("the Agency");

(b) any expenses of the Secretary of State incurred in consequence of the Act;

(c) any increase attributable to the Act in the sums payable out of money so provided under any other enactment;

(2) the payment out of the National Loans Fund of any sums necessary to enable the Secretary of State to make loans to the Agency;

(3) the payment out of the Consolidated Fund of any sums required to fulfil guarantees given by the Treasury in respect of sums borrowed by the Agency.

Resolved, That, for the puposes of any Act resulting from the Housing and Urban Development Bill, it is expedient to authorize—
(a) the making of provision about the payment by the Urban Regeneration Agency to the Secretary of State of sums in respect of surpluses of that Agency;
(b) the payment of any sums into the Consolidated Fund or the National Loans Fund —[Mr. Arbuthnot.]
